title: For Sale:  Stinger missile storage crate, .50 cal riffle case, surplus gun case.
postcontent: Very rare vintage US military surplus crate originally made to hold the Stinger Surface-To-Air missiles. Purchased for a project but no longer need it. Need to get it out of my garage!Made of very lightweight aluminum but is extremely strong. In good condition overall - some original stencils have been painted over and a small ding or two. Nothing that effects function. Outside front has 4 heavy duty latches, back has 4 hinges, sides have 2 carry handles. Also has a pressure relief valve, a humidity indicator and inside has 2 locking hold-open arms to keep the lid up when the case is open. Perfect case for storage, transporting, or shipping your large/expensive firearms like Barrett .50 cal riffles, machine guns, etc. Could be adapted to use as a gun safe and hold or transport several guns as well. There are many "how to" guides online about converting this to various things like rifle cases with wheels, Ammodor cigar humidors, gun safes, etc.The US government (our tax dollars) paid $2,500 each for these cases! That's very expensive for a case, but it housed and protected a Stinger Missile system, which cost $44,000. The Stinger contained very sensitive electronics and a high explosive fragmentation warhead......so these cases needed to be indestructible. I HAVE ALREADY REMOVED the foam original foam inserts so the inside is almost ready for your project - just needs to be cleaned up a bit (picture below shows the foam but again I removed it already...it had to be cut out).The case weighs 47 pounds, and it has the following exterior dimensions: 66 inches in length, 13 inches in depth, and 13.5 inches in height. The interior dimensions are: 63.75 inches in length, 11.125 inches in depth, and 13 inches in height. The bottom half of the case is 8 inches deep, and the top portion is 5 inches deep. Units in better condition sell for $375 - $500. Priced fairly at only $275 due to condition. That much less then I paid for it. I WILL SHIP - shipping will likely be $50-100 by UPS Ground. Feel free to send me your zip code for an estimate.
